 font-style:italic">Control </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">has primarily resulted from the slaughter and disposal of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">BSE-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">affected cattle</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, from prohibiting meat and bone meal derived from animal carcasses being fed back to cattle</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">from preventing those parts of all </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">cattle</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> most likely to be infected (essentially brain, spinal cord including the dorsal root ganglion and parts of the small intestine) from entering the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">human </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">food chain.  The number of affected cattle has declined f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">rom a peak</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> of 36,000 cases in 1992 to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3 in 2012</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">9</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  These measures mostly remain in place.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li s